-- Italy May Cut Incentives for Electric Renewables, Corriere Says
-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 2012-06-03T10:01:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-03/italy-may-cut-incentives-for-electric-renewables-corriere-says.html
Italy may cut incentives on electric
renewables which are still higher than in  Germany , Guido
Bortoni, chairman of the nation’s energy authority, told
 Corriere della Sera  in an interview.  There’s no reason for Italy’s contributions to be higher
than in the rest of Europe, he told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
